Package net.akami.mask.tree

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BinaryTree<T extends Branch>
    A Binary tree handles branch splitting, evaluating and merging with the defined behaviours.
    Branch<T extends Branch>
    The Branch class is a data class that handles a left part and a right part, as well as an expression and a reduced value.
    CalculationTree<T extends Branch>
    CalculationTree is an implementation of the BinaryTree class that manages algebraic calculations, containing the 5 basic binary operations (+ - * / ^) plus the three trigonometric unary operations (sin cos tan).
    DerivativeBranch
    Implementation of the base Branch class.
    DerivativeTree
    Implementation of the CalculationTree class.
    FormatterBranch
    FormatterBranch is an implementation of the branch class that simply redefines the branchFormat method, so it removes the unnecessary brackets in the expression even if it is trigonometric
    FormatterTree  
    ReducerTree
    Most basic implementation of the CalculationTree class.
